Ronald A. WOODLING, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 10612. United States Court of Appeals Sixth Circuit. Oct. 11, 1948. Wm. G. Comb, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. Thos. P. Thornton, of Detroit, Mich., for appellee.

Before HICKS, Chief Judge, and ALLEN and MARTIN, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of counsel for appellant in open court, it is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is, dismissed.
